
▪ Run the image httpd again without attaching any
volumes

[rshdan@192 Downloads]$ docker run httpd


▪ Add html static files to the container and make
sure they are accessible

[rshdan@192 Downloads]$ docker cp staticWebPage.html  hungry_golick:/usr/local/apache2/htdocs/
Successfully copied 2.56kB to hungry_golick:/usr/local/apache2/htdocs/
[rshdan@192 Downloads]$


▪ Commit the container with image name
IMAGE_NAME


[rshdan@localhost Downloads]$ docker commit hungry_golick httpd_image 
sha256:6b3cd978aff89ec053132340dffebe0f7fe768092e6bcefb9e1476e38128065b
[rshdan@localhost Downloads]$ docker image ls
REPOSITORY    TAG       IMAGE ID       CREATED          SIZE
httpd_image   latest    6b3cd978aff8   10 seconds ago   148MB
ubuntu        latest    602eb6fb314b   6 days ago       78.1MB
alpine        latest    aded1e1a5b37   8 weeks ago      7.83MB
nginx         latest    4cad75abc83d   2 months ago     192MB
httpd         latest    10fd72f437c4   2 months ago     148MB
mysql         latest    567107cb6971   2 months ago     797MB
[rshdan@localhost Downloads]$ 




▪ Create a dockerfile for the previous image and
build the image from this dockerfile

FROM httpd
USER root


ADD staticWebPage.html /usr/local/apache2/htdocs
RUN useradd  samy
USER samy

rshdan@192 test]$ docker build . -t httpd:v1.0
